St Patrick's Parish in Stephensville, Wisconsin has discontinued its Original Pig Rassle tournament after 44 years of the tradition .
The event was held in August, 2014, when the pigs were 'punched in the face, kicked, body-slammed, yelled at and thrown onto a barrel'
Global Conservation Group, an animal advocacy group, launched an online petition claiming the event was inhumane to the pigs .
Group also accused the church of being in violation of Wisconsin Chapter 951, Crimes Against Animals, which outlaws cockfighting, dog fighting and any other similar fighting .